    "body": "Hi @caybro it looks as if the wash used for code block formatting just hasn't been implemented to be inline with the designs.\r\n\r\nBoth light and dark theme input and message feed washes are outlined in the Kuba file here:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=232%3A73047&t=NlFVcmmDVed1ts2O-4\r\n\r\nThese colours are much more usable and inline with the design so I think we will be fine if we follow these.\r\n\r\nThe only thing we need to ensure is that the wash of the code snippet is visible on hover. If easy enough to do, perhaps we can implement the Kuba colours and see how well differentiated the code block wash is from the hover wash and tweak values from there if needed.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Compact mode-4\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/207280761-e813e6fa-535d-4c3a-a956-4c0d0a8a5773.png\">\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Compact mode-5\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/207280769-a5894066-92fa-4de4-914c-ef979514c4d6.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Compact mode-2\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/207280841-42871b9d-cbc7-4c34-b5cb-025c38c5b82b.png\">\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Compact mode-3\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/110033914/207280845-acb77a14-cb16-4577-90e8-dcd58ec4cf56.png\">\r\n",
